00:04:58.660 --> 00:05:02.770
Remember if a sound is off
to one side of my head,

00:05:02.770 --> 00:05:06.550
it's going to appear at a higher
sound level in the ear facing

00:05:06.550 --> 00:05:12.190
that sound source than
it will appear in the ear

00:05:12.190 --> 00:05:13.860
away from the sound source.

00:05:13.860 --> 00:05:17.450
So we talked about how big
these cues were last time.

00:05:17.450 --> 00:05:21.800
And they can, for high
frequencies, be maximally 20 dB

00:05:21.800 --> 00:05:24.450
in Interaural Level
Difference, or ILD.

00:05:27.020 --> 00:05:30.820
So those are processed,
at least starting

00:05:30.820 --> 00:05:33.410
in the lateral
superior olive, which

00:05:33.410 --> 00:05:37.080
is another nucleus in the
superior olivary complex, which

00:05:37.080 --> 00:05:41.220
is close to the medial superior
olive we've been talking about.

00:05:41.220 --> 00:05:43.985
So we'll talk about
the process in the LSO.

00:05:45.650 --> 00:05:47.820
Then, we'll talk
about projections

00:05:47.820 --> 00:05:51.080
of that nucleus and the MSO.

00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:52.990
And other parts of
the superior olive

00:05:52.990 --> 00:05:56.270
to the next higher
center in the brainstem,

00:05:56.270 --> 00:06:00.830
which in the auditory pathway is
the Inferior Colliculus, or IC.

00:06:00.830 --> 00:06:04.880
So we'll be talking extensively
about the inferior colliculus,

00:06:04.880 --> 00:06:07.730
which is a large
nucleus in the brainstem

00:06:07.730 --> 00:06:10.100
just caudal to the
superior colliculus

00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:12.800
that you folks talked
about extensively

00:06:12.800 --> 00:06:14.405
in the visual part
of the course.

00:06:16.690 --> 00:06:20.200
In the IC, you have some
interesting neural responses

00:06:20.200 --> 00:06:23.630
that relate to something
called time/intensity trading.

